# .exportignore — LLM Wiki Template
# ====================================
# Patterns matched against export filenames.
# Files matching these patterns are excluded from the SQLite FTS5 index.
# They remain on disk as backup but are NEVER searchable.
#
# Format: one glob pattern per line (matched against filename only).
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# IMPORTANT: Do NOT use single words like "confidential" as patterns —
# use specific labels you explicitly set with --label flag.
# Example: python scripts/export-session.py --trigger manual --label client
# Produces: YYYY-MM-DD_HHMMSS_sessionid_projectname_manual_client.md
# Which matches: *_client_*.md

# ── Always excluded ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*_confidential_*.md

# ── Common sensitive categories (uncomment what applies) ─────────────────────
# *_client_*.md          # client work / NDA
# *_legal_*.md           # legal matters
# *_medical_*.md         # health information
# *_personal_*.md        # personal matters
# *_financial_*.md       # financial details
# *_hr_*.md              # HR / personnel matters
# *_jobsearch_*.md       # job search / interviews

# ── Domain-specific (uncomment if relevant to your work) ─────────────────────
# *_govcon_*.md          # government contracting sensitive data
# *_nda_*.md             # NDA-covered work
# *_audit_*.md           # audit-sensitive material
